---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Why we open-sourced all of it — Ikenga"
	description="Not parts — the whole thing, under Apache-2.0. The reasoning behind open-sourcing the Ikenga workspace, why local-first is the default, and how we sustain it."
	canonical="https://ikenga.dev/open-source"
>

	<!-- Hero -->
	<section class="sk-hero sk-section--flush">
		<div class="sk-wrap">
			<p class="sk-eyebrow">Open source</p>
			<h1 class="sk-display">Why we <em>open-sourced</em> all of it</h1>
			<p class="sk-lede">
				Not parts — the whole thing, under Apache-2.0. Here's the reasoning, in short. The long
				version is in the manifesto and the build-in-public essay, linked below.
			</p>
			<p class="sk-body">
				Platform and all packages are Apache-2.0.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section: The host is the business -->
	<section class="sk-section">
		<div class="sk-wrap">
			<h2 class="sk-h2">The host is the business</h2>
			<p class="sk-body">
				Vercel didn't invent the JavaScript runtime. They built a clean, opinionated host for it,
				and sold the hosting. Workspace AI sits at the same inflection point. We open-source the
				workspace and make our money running it — hosted plans, custom builds, enterprise support.
				We make our money running it, not hiding it.
			</p>
			<p class="sk-body">
				<span class="sk-aside">From <em>The Ikenga Platform Manifesto</em> — the full argument is in the founder's writing.</span>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section: Why local-first -->
	<section class="sk-section">
		<div class="sk-wrap">
			<h2 class="sk-h2">Why local-first</h2>
			<p class="sk-body">
				Your config and your agents' data run on your machine. That means they don't pass through
				someone else's server to be useful, and you can read every line of the code that touches
				them. Local-first isn't a privacy slogan here — it's the default, and the source is
				Apache-2.0 so you can verify it.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Section: Built and run, not a side project -->
	<section class="sk-section">
		<div class="sk-wrap">
			<h2 class="sk-h2">Built and run, not a side project</h2>
			<p class="sk-body">
				We didn't open-source a demo. We built this workspace to run our own company, used it for
				18 months, and shipped the generic half as Ikenga. The cockpit and package manager you see
				are the ones we actually run on. Open-sourcing it means you get the real thing, and we keep
				building it in the open.
			</p>
			<p class="sk-body">
				<span class="sk-aside">From <em>Running a company on AI agents — the useful number isn't 100%</em>.</span>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Foot CTA -->
	<section class="sk-section">
		<div class="sk-wrap sk-obi">
			<h2 class="sk-h2">See for yourself</h2>
			<div class="sk-obi__cta">
				<Button
					href="https://github.com/Royalti-io/ikenga"
					variant="primary"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Star the repo on GitHub
				</Button>
				<Button
					href="https://github.com/Royalti-io/ikenga/blob/main/LICENSE"
					variant="ghost"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Read the license (Apache-2.0)
				</Button>
			</div>
			<p class="sk-body" style="margin-top: var(--space-5);">
				Ready to install? <a class="sk-link" href="/#install">Get Ikenga on your machine.</a>
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

</Layout>

<style>
	.sk-link {
		color: var(--site-accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: color 0.15s ease;
	}
	.sk-link:hover {
		text-decoration: underline;
	}
	.sk-link:focus-visible {
		outline: 2px solid var(--site-accent);
		outline-offset: 2px;
		border-radius: 3px;
	}
</style>
